Description: Linked SQ: a Linked Dataset describing SPARQL queries extracted from the logs of a variety of prominent public SPARQL endpoints. We argue that this dataset has a variety of uses for the SPARQL research community- be it- for example- to generate benchmarks on-the-fly by selecting real-world queries with specific characteristics that we describe- or to conduct analysis of what SPARQL (1.1) query features are most often used to interrogate endpoints- or to characterise the behaviour of the different types of agents that are using these endpoints- or to find out what queries agents are asking about a given resource- etc.
Sources: Web:Absent Name:Muhammad Saleem; Intizar Ali; Qaiser Mehmood; Aidan Hogan; Axel-Cyrille Ngonga Ngomo Email:Absent
